Class SolQueueReceiver

    public class SolQueueReceiver
extends SolMessageConsumer
implements QueueReceiver, SolEventSource, FlowEventHandler
    Solace QueueReceiver implementation. Does not support concurrent use.

        Sets the message consumer's MessageListener.

        Setting the message listener to null is the equivalent of unsetting the message listener for the message consumer.

        The effect of calling MessageConsumer.setMessageListener while messages are being consumed by an existing listener or the consumer is being used to consume messages synchronously is undefined.

      • addSolEventListener

        public void addSolEventListener(SolEventListener listener,
                       long eventTypeMask)
                         throws JMSException
        Description copied from interface: SolEventSource
        Registers a SolEventListener to receive events of types specified in eventTypeMask (possible types are defined in com.solacesystems.jms.SolEvent). A SolEventListener can be added more than once. If the application adds the same SolEventListener with a different eventTypeMask, the net effect is cumulative. Using the same eventTypeMask has no effect. To de-register or remove the SolEventListner instance, call removeSolEventListner() If the SolEventSource does not emit an event type specified in the eventTypeMask then a com.solacesystems.jms.ConfigurationException is thrown
        Specified by:
        addSolEventListener in interface SolEventSource
        Parameters:
        listener - parameter
        eventTypeMask - parameter
        Throws:
        JMSException - on error
